from __future__ import print_function, division

from smt.problems import Sphere, NdimRobotArm, Rosenbrock
from smt.sampling_methods import LHS
from smt.surrogate_models import LS, QP, KPLS, KRG, KPLSK, GEKPLS, MGP
try:
    from smt.surrogate_models import IDW, RBF, RMTC, RMTB
    compiled_available = True
except:
    compiled_available = False

try:
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    plot_status = True
except:
    plot_status = False

import scipy.interpolate

from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

ndim = 2 #    ()
ndoe = 20 #   

fun = Rosenbrock(ndim = ndim) # Black-box   (e.g., ,  )

Step2: 실험계획법 (DOE)¶

In [3]:
#  
#       (orthogonality)  (space-filling)  
sampling = LHS(xlimits = fun.xlimits, random_state = 1) #    
# Optimize the design using the Enhanced Stochastic Evolutionary algorithm (ESE)
# sampling = LHS(xlimits=fun.xlimits, criterion='ese', random_state=1) #    
xt = sampling(ndoe)

print("Input data",xt) #

Step 5: 모델 검증¶

In [7]:
#    
ntest = 200
sampling = LHS(xlimits=fun.xlimits, criterion='ese', random_state=1)
xtest = sampling(ntest)
ytest = fun(xtest)
In [8]:
# Prediction of the validation points
y_pred = sm.predict_values(xtest) #       
print('Kriging,  err: '+ str(compute_rms_error(sm,xtest,ytest)))

if plot_status:
    # Plot the function, the prediction and the 95% confidence interval based on
    # the MSE
    fig = plt.figure()
    plt.plot(ytest, ytest, '-', label='$y_{true}$')
    plt.plot(ytest, y_pred, 'r.', label='$\hat{y}$')
   
    plt.xlabel('$y_{true}$')
    plt.ylabel('$\hat{y}$')
    
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('Kriging model: validation of the prediction model')   

if plot_status:
    plt.show()

Kriging,  err: 0.0005665998329528192

In [10]:
# Plot the surrogate model in 3D 
x = np.linspace(-2, 2, 50)
resSM = []
varSM = []
for x0 in x:
    for x1 in x:
        resSM.append(sm.predict_values(np.array([[x0,x1]])))
        varSM.append(sm.predict_variances(np.array([[x0,x1]])))
In [11]:
#  
resSM = np.array(resSM)
resSM = resSM.reshape((50,50)).T
varSM = np.array(varSM)
varSM = varSM.reshape((50,50)).T                     
X,Y = np.meshgrid(x,x)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))

                       linewidth=0, antialiased=False,alpha=0.5)
ax.scatter(xtest[:,0], xtest[:,1], ytest, zdir='z', marker='.', c='g', s=100, label='Test')
ax.scatter(xtest[:,0], xtest[:,1], y_pred, zdir='z', marker = 'x', c='r', s=100, label='Prediction')

                       linewidth=0, antialiased=False, alpha=0.5)

In [13]:
ndim = 2 #    ()
ndoe = 20 #   

fun = Rosenbrock(ndim = ndim) # Black-box   (e.g., ,  )

#  
#       (orthogonality)  (space-filling)  
sampling = LHS(xlimits = fun.xlimits, criterion = 'ese', random_state = 1) #    
xt = sampling(ndoe)

#    (    )
yt = fun(xt)

#  (Main process)
initial_theta = [1e-2]*ndim #   
sm = KRG(theta0 = initial_theta,print_prediction = False)
sm.set_training_values(xt,yt[:,0]) #  
sm.train() #  


#  
print("initial theta values",  initial_theta)
print("optimal theta values",  sm.optimal_theta)

#     ()
x_want = np.array([[1.2, 1.2]]) #  
y_want = sm.predict_values(x_want) # 
s2_want = np.sqrt(sm.predict_variances(x_want)) #  
y_real = fun(x_want) #

ndim = 4 #    ()
ndoe = 40 #   

fun = Rosenbrock(ndim=ndim) # Black-box   (e.g., ,  )

#  
#       (orthogonality)  (space-filling)  
design_xlimits = np.array([[-3,3],[-4,4],[-10,1],[-3,5]])
sampling = LHS(xlimits = design_xlimits, criterion = 'ese', random_state = 1) #    
xt = sampling(ndoe)

print(" ",design_xlimits)
print("  ",xt)

#    (    )
yt = fun(xt)

#  (Main process)
initial_theta = [1e-1]*ndim #   
sm = KRG(theta0=initial_theta,print_prediction = False)
sm.set_training_values(xt,yt[:,0]) #  
sm.train() #  


#  
print("initial theta values",  initial_theta)
print("optimal theta values",  sm.optimal_theta)

#     ()
x_want = np.array([[1.2, 1.2, 1.2, 1.2]]) #  
y_want = sm.predict_values(x_want) # 
s2_want = np.sqrt(sm.predict_variances(x_want)) #  
y_real = fun(x_want) #
